'''Christina Sharpe''' is a scholar of [[English literature]] and [[Black studies|Black Studies]]. She is most well-known for her books ''In the Wake: On Blackness and'' ''Being''<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/940520601|title=In the wake : on Blackness and being|last=Elizabeth,|first=Sharpe, Christina|isbn=9780822362838|location=Durham|oclc=940520601}}</ref> and ''Monstrous Intimacies: Making Post-Slavery Subjects''.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/574955806|title=Monstrous intimacies : making post-slavery subjects|last=Elizabeth.|first=Sharpe, Christina|date=2010|publisher=Duke University Press|isbn=9780822345916|location=Durham, NC|oclc=574955806}}</ref> She is currently a professor at York University's department of humanities and the newly created Black Canadian Studies certificate program.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bcs.huma.laps.yorku.ca/2018/06/christina-sharpe-leading-scholar-in-black-diaspora-studies-joins-black-studies-program-at-york-university/|title=Christina Sharpe, leading scholar in Black Diaspora Studies, joins Black Studies program at York University {{!}} Faculty of Liberal Arts & Professional Studies|website=bcs.huma.laps.yorku.ca|language=en-US|access-date=2018-10-25}}</ref>
